f F8 usefullness<br>- yes/no i also have the same problem<br><br><br>such input would be much appreciated.<br>-d<br><br>==============================================<br>EDIT: results so far:<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   A. Solutions:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>- <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>'Use center screen' ('U') key</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> works as it has before. This will target the NPC in the small region around the middle of your screen. If the NPC you want to f8 is around that area, and quite often they are, this will help you out. Not god-sent, but sure as hell better than mousing it.<br><br>EDIT2: this works worse than I hoped - the range when it works is simply too short.  any blue con will already be chasing you, even the dumb spiders in Velks on lvl 60, if you get close enough to them for 'U' to work.  At this point you can just as easily hit f8 for same results. /sigh<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   B. Bug theories:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   1. NPC movement</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. f8 success is determined by whether the NPC is moving. supposedly some time ago mobs standing still were made not send position updates. <br><br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Pros</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->: <br>-couple people reporting that moving NPCs get f8'd more often than stationary ones. need clarification if it's 'more often' or 'always' and 'never' with moving /non-moving respectively (aside: kinda hard to test reproduceably if it's just 'more often'). <br>-f8 not working more often in dungeons.<br><br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Cons</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->: <br>-Rooted and/or mezzed mobs are easily f8'd in camp.<br><br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   2. NPC hatelist</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. f8 success is determined by whether or not you are on the NPC's hatelist.<br><br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Pros</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->: tests show that f8 is immideately successful as soon as the mob starts chasing you / swinging at you (without necessarily connecting) when you couldnt target the same NPC from the same spacial orientation before entering its hatelist. (aside: need to test whether f8'ing a mezzed mob is just as easy if it's memblurred until /ass on the mob gives you nothing)<br><br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Cons</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->: people reporting having better success f8'ing NPCs if: i) you clear target window first ii) target is moving. If hatelist related, these improvements are not explained.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udiondlion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dion DLion</A> at: 3/20/02 6:18:16 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwrexen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wrexen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/02 6:28:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22889.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nearest NPC auto-targeting broken... why noone screaming</span><hr size=1> I'm currently using 'U' to target although that sucks pretty bad too, but it does seem to hit mobs that the new F8 misses <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uleodido.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leodido</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/02 7:06:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22889.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nearest NPC auto-targeting broken... why noone 