 screaming</span><hr size=1> I have this problem all the time, some zones it's pretty pointless even trying to use f8.<br><br>I seem to have particular problems if:<br>1. you have yourself targetted<br>2. you're trying to switch between mobs with the same names, or to/from a mob's pet<br>3. the mobs are small<br><br>Problem 2 is also a pain when you're clicking on a mob directly - hard to convince it to switch targets withouth hitting escape first <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=43564">Core</a><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=43574">Dworkin</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udiondlion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dion DLion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/02 8:49:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22889.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nearest NPC auto-targeting broken... why noone screaming</span><hr size=1> Interesting test:<br><br>-throw on some invis and come up to a green con mob really close, so that there is no mistake about it<br>-hit f8 until the cows come home to be perfectly sure it's still broken and you cannot get it on target <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>-drop invis and start banging your f8<br><br>Results:<br>You should be able to f8 the mob immideately as it starts swinging at you even *before* the mob actually connects.  Note: mob connecting taints the test 'cause it becomes the target automatically if it